    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — FEA F1717 compression-bending QoI",
    "description": "Sobol variance-based global sensitivity analysis (N=4096 quasi-random LHS samples, Saltelli estimator) was performed varying 14 input parameters including titanium-alloy elastic modulus (±5%), screw outer diameter tolerance (±0.05 mm), thread root radius (±0.02 mm), rod modulus (±3%), pedicle screw insertion depth (±1 mm), and polyacetal block modulus (±8%). Dominant first-order indices for yield force QoI: screw root radius (S1=0.31), titanium elastic modulus (S1=0.27), and rod modulus (S1=0.19) together account for 77% of output variance; total-order indices confirm negligible higher-order interaction terms (ST–S1 < 0.04 for all factors), justifying a focused UQ propagation strategy concentrating sampling effort on these three dominant parameters."
